vulnerabilities.title: Prototype Pollution in madlib-object-utils
vulnerabilities.description: madlib-object-utils before 0.1.7 is vulnerable to Prototype Pollution via setValue.

vulnerabilities.title: Prototype Pollution in madlib-object-utils
vulnerabilities.description: The package madlib-object-utils before version 0.1.8 is vulnerable to Prototype Pollution via the `setValue` method, as it allows an attacker to merge object prototypes into it. *Note:* This vulnerability derives from an incomplete fix of [CVE-2020-7701](https://security.snyk.io/vuln/SNYK-JS-MADLIBOBJECTUTILS-598676)
